{
  "texts": [
    "The routing mechanism in MoE could inspire a novel class of aggregation strategies in FL, where dynamic data-driven approaches could allocate model contributions in a similar manner.",
    "Exploring aggregation strategies that mirror MoE's routing scheme and adapting it to the distributed nature of FL, could inspire new FedFM model aggregation methods.",
    "Such exploration might involve designing algorithms that not only learn from local data, but also intelligently decide how to combine local updates to form a robust global model, potentially redefining the FedFM aggregation approach as a learned component rather than a fixed rule.MoE-FL [79] uses MoE to aggregate a robust global model on the server.",
    "It assumes trust between the server and clients where each client shares partial data with the server.",
    "Although the produced robust aggregation model can filter outliers (poisoned/corrupted/outdated client models), sharing partial local data may be prohibited in most FL applications with privacy requirements."
  ]
}